SIMPLE: hint
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hint
<hw>Hint</hw> <pr>(h⟦icr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hinted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hinting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>henten</ets>,
<ets>hinten</ets>, to seize, to catch, AS. <ets>hentan</ets> to pursue,
take, seize; or Icel. <ets>ymta</ets> to mutter, <ets>ymtr</ets> a
muttering, Dan. <ets>ymte</ets> to whisper. ⟦root⟧36. Cf.
<er>Hent</er>.]</ety> <def>To bring to mind by a slight mention or
remote allusion; to suggest in an indirect manner; <as>as, to
<ex>hint</ex> a suspicion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Just <qex>hint</qex> a fault and hesitate dislike.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To suggest; intimate; insinuate; imply.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hint
<hw>Hint</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make an indirect reference,
suggestion, or allusion; to allude vaguely to something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We whisper, and <qex>hint</qex>, and chuckle.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To hint at</b></col>, <cd>to allude to lightly,
indirectly, or cautiously.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To allude; refer; glance; touch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hint
<hw>Hint</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A remote allusion; slight mention;
intimation; insinuation; a suggestion or reminder, without a full
declaration or explanation; also, an occasion or motive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>hint</qex> of woe⟦br⟧
Is common.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>hint</qex> malevolent, the look oblique.</q>
<rj><qau>Hannah More.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Suggestion; allusion. See
<er>Suggestion</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hinterland</ent>⟦br⟧
